quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  67,27,"Then when they see it<sup>7</sup> approaching closer, the faces of the disbelievers will be distressed, and it will be said, “This is what you were asking for<sup>8</sup>.”","[7] The punishment on the Day of Judgment of which they were warned.\n [8] As they were challenging their prophets, saying, ""Bring upon us the punishment, if you are truthful."""
  67,28,"Say, “What do you think<sup>9</sup>, if Allah causes me and those who are with me to die or shows us mercy, who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment?”","[9] i.e., Inform me."
  67,29,"Say, “He is the Most Compassionate; we believe in Him and put our trust in Him. You will come to know who is clearly misguided.”",""
  67,30,"Say, “What do you think, if your water were to sink deep into the earth, who can bring you flowing water?”",""
  68,1,"Nūn<sup>1</sup>. By the pen and what they [i.e., the angels] write [in the Records of deeds],","[1] See footnote 2:1."
  68,2,"By the grace of your Lord [O Prophet], you are not a madman.",""
  68,3,"You will surely have a never-ending reward.",""
  68,4,"Indeed, you are of a great moral character.",""
  68,5,"Soon you will see and they will see,",""
  68,6,"which of you is afflicted with madness.",""
  68,7,"Indeed, your Lord alone knows best who has strayed from His way and those who are rightly guided.",""
  68,8,"So do not obey the deniers.",""
  68,9,"They wish that you would compromise so they would too compromise.",""
  68,10,"And do not obey every disgraceful swearer,",""
  68,11,"backbiter, gossip-monger,",""
  68,12,"withholder of good, transgressor, sinful,",""
  68,13,"coarse, and furthermore, an illegitimate child<sup>2</sup>.","[2] i.e., falsely claiming a particular lineage. It refers to Al-Walīd ibn al-Mughīrah (See also 74:11-25) or possibly Al-Akhnas ibn Shurayq."
  68,14,"Simply because he has wealth and children,",""
  68,15,"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, “Ancient fables!”",""
